`Nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos` is defined in `Mathlib/Data/Nat/Defs.lean`. It states `0 < n → n.pred.succ = n` (i.e. `Nat.succ (Nat.pred n) = n` when `0 < n`). Note that in current Mathlib the lemma uses the namespaced name `Nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos` (capital `N`); the lowercase `nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos` is the old Lean 3 / mathlib3 name. If you're on Lean 4 / Mathlib 4, use `Nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos`, e.g. `rw [Nat.succ_pred_eq_of_pos h]` where `h : 0 < n`.
